<font color="#FF0000">THANKS!  FROM A VET</font><br>
<tt>Fri Feb 21 20:13:25 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I post on this site regularly and it is a joy to finally get the recognition that I have craved, wanted, searched for so long.  The recognition is that what was done was not in vain.  That the innocense was lost for a cause that people can see was not the warrior's fault.  That those names on the wall mean something other than grief and sorrow. <br>
This site gives me and many others an opportunity to share, vent, connect and heal. <br>
I am proud to call all those who served &quot;Brother&quot;.  We are brothers of a unique experience.  That until just recently was shared in veteran's hospitals, counseling centers and breaskfasts of vets getting together.  Initially, the VFW or the American Legion didn't want us because we &quot;lost the war&quot;.<br>
Well folks,  I'm here to tell you; &quot;We were winning when I left!&quot;.  And today I feel that we can start to develop a winning feeling through this site.  Thanks PBS, from a vet. <br>

<p><code>-- cbotkins@visuallink.com  (Chet Botkins) </code><p>


